title.@value: Double outlet right ventricle with subaortic or doubly committed ventricular septal defect and pulmonary stenosis, Fallot type

definition.@value: A congenital cardiovascular malformation that is a variant of double outlet right ventricle with concordant atrioventricular connections, a subaortic or doubly-committed (with absence or deficiency of the conal septum) ventricular septal defect, and pulmonary outflow tract obstruction.
